      "day": 1,
      "title": "Agents in the Real World",
      "start_time": "9:00",
      "end_time": "9:45",
      "duration_minutes": 45,
      "stage": "Agents",
      "set_the_stage": "We open with the practitioner's view. Before we touch any code, we answer the questions a working professional actually asks: what is an agent, where does it help, where does it fall down, and how do we keep it safe.\n\nI'll walk you through these slides one idea at a time, with a wrong way and a right way for each. We'll slow down on the risks and on keeping a human in the loop; that is the grown-up part of this conversation.\n\nBy the end, you should be able to say in one sentence what an agent reads, decides, and produces, and name the one place it could quietly go wrong.",
      "nav": "Agents"
    },
    {
