      "phase": "day",
      "session_type": "build",
      "id": "2",
      "number": 2,
      "day": 1,
      "title": "The Humanics of AI",
      "start_time": "9:45",
      "end_time": "10:45",
      "duration_minutes": 60,
      "stage": "Humanics",
      "set_the_stage": "This is the thinking layer, and it is where the real skill lives. The best agent-builders are not the fastest typists; they are the clearest thinkers. We'll work through first principles, systems thinking, decomposition, and how to define what good even means.\n\nNone of this is abstract. Every habit here points straight at the recruitment agent we build next. Breaking a task into atoms, seeing the whole pipe, and framing a sharp question are exactly what will make that agent easy to design.\n\nTake these seriously and the build becomes the easy part. The clear thinking is what you'll carry into every agent you ever make.",
      "nav": "Humanics"
    },
