      "day": 1,
      "title": "The Mechanics of AI",
      "start_time": "11:00",
      "end_time": "11:45",
      "duration_minutes": 45,
      "stage": "Mechanics",
      "set_the_stage": "Now the building blocks, kept deliberately simple: a model (text in, text out), a prompt (your instructions), structured output (neat data, not prose), and a key (just a password).\n\nThen the anatomy every agent shares, input to brain to output, and the one move that makes real agents work: splitting the job into three single-purpose agents that hand clean data down the line.\n\nThis is our bridge from idea to build. I'll keep it tight and concrete, and resist the urge to go down any rabbit holes about how models work inside.",
      "nav": "Mechanics"
